Cloud Computing and Distribution System

There are 2 outline : 
    1. OCI Services Category 
        OCI stands for Oracle Cloud Infrastructure. There are three category of Cloud services, IaaS, PaaS, and SaaS. 
    2. OCI Core Services 
        There are 5 services of OCI Core Services, Compute, Storage, Networking, Identity and Access Management (IAM) 
        and Database Cloud Service. 
            A. Compute 
                OCI Compute Service consists of 5 components, namely bare metal, dedicated virtual hosts, virtual machines,
                container engines and functions. 
            B. Storage 
                There are 5 storage services supported by OCI, namely block volume, local NVME, file storage, object storage and archive storage.
            C. Networking 
                VCN allows users to manage existing networks in a cloud environment. In this case, we can set the IP Address, create subnets and route tables, also configure the firewall. 
            D. IAM 
                IAM (Identity and Access Management ) lets you control who has access to the cloud resources you own, and what type of access they have, and to specific resources.
                IAM policies are documents that define who and how can be used to access resources.
            E. Database Cloud Service 
                Oracle is the only public cloud that supports VM database systems, offering extremely fast provisioning. OCI also supports bare metal database systems,
                which are extremely fast. OCI has a choice Oracle Cluster Databases, also known as Real Application Clusters, or RAC, 
                have been the choice for managing high availability and performance for more than 20 years.


            

          
    
    
